title: Thea Gilmore: Ambitious Outsiders + The Threads EP
description:
Ambitious Outsiders is 17 uncollected B-Sides, singles and one-offs by Thea Gilmore. Also included: the limited edition tour EP, "The Threads". With album artwork (on Ambitious Outsiders) by Sophie Mazingarbe and Roly the Non-Wonder Dog.


Complete tracklisting (in alphabetical order; I do have track numbers embedded in the files but you can feel free to make your own list) is as follows:

Ambitious Outsiders:

All tracks by Thea Gilmore unless otherwise indicated

Even Gods Do - from "Where's Neil When You Need Him", the Neil Gaiman tribute album
Expensive Clothes - Mainstream CD1 B-Side
Fever Beats - 2001 single
Goodnight Copenhagen - Mainstream CD2 B-Side
Honesty Box - Old Soul B-Side
Hooligansville - Juliet CD2 B-Side
I Want To Tell You (George Harrison) - from Revolver Reloaded, one of those MOJO giveaway CDs
It All Gets Buried in the End - Cheap Tricks B-Side
Let the Blue Sky In - Cheap Tricks B-Side
Let's Make a Scene - Mainstream CD1 B-Side
Lightning (Nigel Stonier) - Juliet CD1 B-Side and a cover of a song written and originally recorded by her future husband
Like Lead - Juliet CD2 B-Side
Throw the Bouquet - Juliet CD1 B-Side
To the Bone - Mainstream CD2 B-Side
You and Frank Sinatra - YouTube exclusive, live from her living room

The Threads:

Teacher Teacher
Are You Ready?
Icarus Wind
The Parting Glass
